Ratings agency Moody s placed South Africa on review for downgrade &#8211; following cabinet reshuffle.The decision to initiate a review for downgrade was prompted buy abrupt change in leadership of key government institutions, it said in a statement. South Africa s sovereign credit rating is currently two notches above non-investment grade at Baa2. This action had raised questions regarding On Monday the new Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba attempted to reassure the country and ratings agencies by saying that only the executive had changed, the National Treasury remained strong and resilient and there had been no policy change. This following a cabinet reshuffle in which Pravin Gordhan and his deputy Mcebisi Jonas were fired.On Monday S&amp;P downgraded South Africa sovereign credit rating to BB+ commonly known as junk status. The moves have been met with criticism by some analysts saying the rating agencies were attempting to influence the political climate in the country. S&amp;P said in its press statement that internal government and party divisions could, we believe, delay fiscal and structural reforms, and potentially erode the trust that had been established between business leaders and labour representatives (including in the critical mining sector) . An additional risk is that businesses may now choose to withhold investment decisions that would otherwise have supported economic growth. We think that ongoing tensions and the potential for further event risk could weigh on investor confidence and exchange rates, and potentially drive increases in real interest rates. -ANN7 reporter